						<p class="p1"><a href="http://9to5mac.com/2014/05/14/apple-reportedly-acknowledges-hijacked-text-message-problem/messages-4/" rel="attachment wp-att-323200"><img data-attachment-id="323200" data-permalink="https://9to5mac.com/2014/05/14/apple-reportedly-acknowledges-hijacked-text-message-problem/messages-4/" data-orig-file="https://9to5mac.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/6/2014/05/messages.png" data-orig-size="861,415" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;}" data-image-title="messages" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://9to5mac.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/6/2014/05/messages.png?w=655" data-large-file="https://9to5mac.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/6/2014/05/messages.png?w=861" title="How to fix the iOS text message bug causing iPhone crashing/reboot (U: Apple statement, watches too)" loading="lazy" class=" size-large wp-image-323200 aligncenter" src="https://9to5mac.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/6/2014/05/messages.png?w=704" alt="messages" width="704" height="339" srcset="https://9to5mac.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/6/2014/05/messages.png 861w, https://9to5mac.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/6/2014/05/messages.png?resize=155,75 155w, https://9to5mac.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/6/2014/05/messages.png?resize=655,316 655w, https://9to5mac.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/6/2014/05/messages.png?resize=768,370 768w, https://9to5mac.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/6/2014/05/messages.png?resize=350,169 350w, https://9to5mac.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/6/2014/05/messages.png?resize=150,72 150w" sizes="(max-width: 704px) 100vw, 704px" /></a></p>
<p class="p1"><em>Update: <a href="http://www.theguardian.com/technology/2015/may/28/iphone-text-message-bug-crash-apple-watch-ipad-mac" target="_blank">The Guardian</a> notes that the bug also crashes the Apple Watch when you try to reply to a message.</em></p>
<p class="p1"><span class="s1">Today news is flying around regarding <a href="http://9to5mac.com/2015/05/26/ios-messages-crash-bug/" target="_blank">an iOS bug that causes the Messages app to crash</a> and iPhones to reboot when a certain string of text is received. There isn’t an official fix from Apple yet, but there are a few workarounds and fixes that you can do in the meantime before Apple patches the bug. </span></p>
<p class="p1"><span class="s1">Here are a few fixes that users have discovered and sent in:</span><span id="more-381712"></span><ins class="adsbygoogle author_ad"
			style="display:block;"
			data-ad-host="ca-host-pub-5506057612223327"
			data-ad-client="ca-pub-6199326417075544"
			data-ad-format="auto"></ins>
		<script>
			(adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).push({});
		</script></p>
<ul>
<li class="p1"><span class="s1"><strong>&#8212;</strong>Have the person who sent you the malicious message send another message effectively canceling out the initial strand</span></li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li class="p1"><span class="s1"><strong>&#8212;</strong>Alternatively, send yourself a message via Siri, the share sheet, or from your Mac.</span></li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li class="p1"><span class="s1"><strong>&#8212;</strong>Another reader notes that “sending a photo to the contact via the Photos app can allow them to access the message history and delete the conversation”</span></li>
</ul>
<p>These fixes should do the trick while we await an official fix from Apple in an upcoming software update. An Apple spokesperson already confirmed it&#8217;s working on a fix that will deploy in a future update:</p>
<p style="padding-left:30px;"><em>“We are aware of an iMessage issue caused by a specific series of unicode characters and we will make a fix available in a software update.”</em></p>
<p class="p1"><a href="http://bit.ly/1J4B56I" target="_blank"><span class="s1"><img data-attachment-id="381906" data-permalink="https://9to5mac.com/2015/05/28/moleskine-iphone-app/9to5mac-3/" data-orig-file="https://9to5mac.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/6/2015/05/9to5mac.jpg?quality=82&amp;strip=all" data-orig-size="704,90" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="9to5MAC" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://9to5mac.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/6/2015/05/9to5mac.jpg?quality=82&amp;strip=all&amp;w=655" data-large-file="https://9to5mac.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/6/2015/05/9to5mac.jpg?quality=82&amp;strip=all&amp;w=704" title="How to fix the iOS text message bug causing iPhone crashing/reboot (U: Apple statement, watches too)" loading="lazy" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-381906" src="https://9to5mac.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/6/2015/05/9to5mac.jpg" alt="9to5MAC" width="704" height="90" srcset="https://9to5mac.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/6/2015/05/9to5mac.jpg 704w, https://9to5mac.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/6/2015/05/9to5mac.jpg?resize=155,20 155w, https://9to5mac.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/6/2015/05/9to5mac.jpg?resize=655,84 655w, https://9to5mac.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/6/2015/05/9to5mac.jpg?resize=350,45 350w, https://9to5mac.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/6/2015/05/9to5mac.jpg?resize=150,19 150w" sizes="(max-width: 704px) 100vw, 704px" /> </span></a></p>
